args: You look exhausted. Is it Durant?
Indeed. Whenever I try to heal him,\nhe flies into a fury and refuses.\nI can see why they call him ＂Mad Dog.＂
I have not been struggling alone, however.
We can't thank you enough for helpin' out\nthe boss—and us too, of course.
It's nothing. I never could've left him\nlike that.
I was impressed by you two, by the way.
You didn't even hesitate to protect your\nleader with your lives. Not many people\ncould do that.
Yeah, well, we owe him our lives.
You mean because he risked his own to\nsave you the other day?
Sure—but that wasn't the first time.\nWithout Durant, we'd be dead in\nsome alley in Valkaheim.
I've heard that city is a cold meritocracy.

Man, you've got no idea. We were livin'
like garbage back then, until Durant
found us and gave us the strength
that comes from pack life.
Doesn't matter where ya come from,\nor how strong ya are—together,\nyou're always stronger!
Keep lettin' this town smack ya around,\nand you're just gonna be helpless mutts\nforever!
I suppose his coarseness is a product\nof surviving in Valkaheim.
Yeah. Pretty words don't mean\nnothin' there.
He's not all bad, though. He took in a stray\npuppy and raised it, for one.
Took a couple'a days, but we eventually\nrealized it was really a wolf pup.\nDefinitely ate like one...
I struggle to picture him nursing anything\nbut a sore jaw.
Eh, that's just Durant. But lemme tell ya,\nthere's no one we respect more!
I believe it. And I hope he can open his\nheart to us one day too.
Oh, I suspect we won't be waiting long.\nYou have your own knack for winning\nothers over.
But in order to see that happen, he must\nfirst allow me to treat his wounds.
Durant! Where are you going?!\nYour wounds have yet to heal!
Hey, you should really listen to Cleo.
Why are you two just standing there?!\nStop him, for goodness sake!
No can do.\nWe know what this means to him.
Do you know where he's going?
He's got a job only he can do.
So, you're back... Wait, are those wounds?!\nWhat happened?!
What do you care? Not like we're friends.
Maybe not, but I think anyone would be\nworried seeing you like this.
What's your deal, anyway? You just let\nanyone off the street into your castle?
Little slow in the head, huh?\nGood luck rulin' a kingdom.
I make judgments when I have to.

Say your most trusted pal betrays you.
If you don't put him down, the rest of
the pack'll be in danger. But then, you
have so many memories together...
Good times, bad times; any time ya\ncan think of, you've had it with this guy.
What would you do? Take their life?\nCould ya even DO that?
Me? I'd kill 'em right there.\nFor the sake of the pack.
That's my job as the boss.
Your job... Wait, did you go out today to—
Lemme make somethin' crystal clear.\nYou're lackin' as a leader, blondie.
You've got ideals and pretty words, but do\nya have the raw GRIT it takes to make your\ndreams happen?!
Crawlin' though garbage, lying, stealing...\nDoin' whatever it takes to survive.
And then when the time comes, pullin'\nyourself up outta the muck to move up\nthe food chain.
That's how this world is. Unless ya get\nyour hands dirty, you won't change a\ndamn thing in this kingdom.
One thing you do have is strength, and I\ncan put that to good use. So go on, bend\nthe ol' knee and swear allegiance to me.
Whaddya mean, ＂no＂? I'm askin' ya nicely,\nblondie—don't go coppin' an attitude.
Say whatever you want—but I'm going to\ngovern this land my way.
The idea of my allies betraying me is\nsomething I'd rather not think about...
But if that time does come, I'll be sure to\nmake a proper decision.
A good, even decision that I won't regret.
I'm going back to my room. You should\nthink about doing the same. Good night.
Every time he opens his damn mouth,\nnothin' but pretty words fall out!\nMakes me SICK!
The only way to get what you want is by\ngettin' down and dirty.
You can't keep clean and expect to make\nanything happen. The world doesn't work\nlike that!
...Right? I mean, if it did, what would that\nmean for me, covered in the blood of my\ncomrades...?
